        "timestamp": "2018-04-11 22:36:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@DeWayne I don't know if you saw my other comment but a good way to update gerrit changes is to amend the patch. This keeps review and patch history together and its useful later. The process is: 'git fetch https://gerrit.onap.org/r/so refs/changes/57/42357/1 && git checkout FETCH_HEAD' (look for download button in upper right of gerrit change), make changes, 'git add -A -p', 'git commit --amend', push change.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
