        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-11 22:45:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI took a look at this earlier. I didn't get to the solution, but adding the aria-client dependency on a clean master tip causes the exact failures we are seeing in jenkins/local builds. So something about this dependency addition seems to be at issue:\n<dependency>\n  <groupId>org.onap.so</groupId>\n  <artifactId>aria-client</artifactId>\n  <version>${project.version}</version>\n</dependency>",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "fee0ed1e974e79d895e46ccd5e50385172636d45",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1595,
          "name": "DeWayne Filppi",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dfilppi@gmail.com",
          "username": "dfilppi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-11 22:50:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nInteresting that this would break an sdnc unit test that doesn't use it.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f79a0dfb8628721052d4232f3880eed1353ae59b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1595,
          "name": "DeWayne Filppi",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dfilppi@gmail.com",
          "username": "dfilppi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-11 23:01:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOddly.  It's a test that expects a ClassFormatException for some reason, and when it doesn't get it, it fails.  So maybe the question is \"why would you have a unit test that expects a ClassFormatException\".  Put another way, maybe things are *not* broken now, and that's what breaks the test.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "38ea17029f4ad243509d714b63a1de0372ae75af",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1595,
          "name": "DeWayne Filppi",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dfilppi@gmail.com",
          "username": "dfilppi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-12 21:01:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSo who is responsible for that test?  Let's get rid of it, unless there is some logical reason for it's existence.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
